*** Pre-Deploy of adhoc with maven:
0. Have ant & maven installed. JAVA_HOME should be set in shell that maven will run from.
1. Edit install.properties in marklogic-db-setup/trunk/ml-user-management
2. Change 'hostname' to deploy target instance IP or hostname.
3. Change 'securityuser' and 'securitypassword' to your credentials on that ML instance
4. Change 'port' to an xdbc server you can deploy to


*** Deploy of adhoc with maven:
1. Simply call run "ant" and it'll deploy to 8006!
$ ant


*** Usage:
Give the data-explorer role to anyone who is not an admin that requires access to the app.